readability_reflection: I found string interpolation to be more readable because it allowed me to understand what is meant to be there. For example, the website/file examples felt more readable when I saw {domain} as opposed to + the domain + or {user} as opposed to + the user name +.
comprehension_debugging: Yes, using string interpolation felt like it sped up my ability to understand and debug code because it did not pluses around it, making it easier to read.
preference_rationale: I would prefer string interpolation. I liked how it looked less intrusive than what is required for string concatenation.
learning_curve: I believe that my prior familiarity with string interpolation and concatenation allowed me to have a bit of an easier time understanding what would be printed compared to someone with no experience.
